@startuml bidding-flow
title Real-Time Bidding Activity

|Buyer|
start
:Open active auction page;

|Bidding Service|
:Establish WebSocket connection\nfor this auction;
:Subscribe buyer to auction channel;
:Send current highest bid snapshot;

|Buyer|
:View live auction state\n(current bid, time remaining,\nbid history);
:Enter bid amount;
:Submit bid;

|Bidding Service|
:Receive bid request;

fork
  note: Concurrent bid\nconflict window
  :Acquire optimistic lock\non auction row;
fork again
  :Another buyer submits\nbid simultaneously;
end fork

:Resolve concurrent bids\n(database-level locking,\nhighest bid wins);

:Validate bid amount;
if (Bid > current highest + min increment?) then (yes)
  if (Auction still ACTIVE?) then (yes)
    if (Buyer is not current leader?) then (yes)
      :Persist new Bid entity;
      :Update auction.currentHighestBid;

      fork
        :Broadcast updated bid\nto all WebSocket subscribers\n(current highest, bidder alias);
      fork again
        :Send outbid email\nto previous highest bidder;
      fork again
        :Send bid confirmation\nto current bidder;
      end fork

      |Buyer|
      :See live bid update\non auction page;

    else (no — already leading)
      :Return error: You are\nalready the highest bidder;
      |Buyer|
      :Display error message;
    endif
  else (no)
    :Return error: Auction has ended;
    |Buyer|
    :Display auction closed message;
    stop
  endif
else (no)
  :Return error: Bid too low\n(show minimum required);
  |Buyer|
  :Adjust bid amount;
  :Resubmit;
endif

|Bidding Service|
:Check anti-snipe rule\n(bid in last 30 seconds?);
if (Yes) then (yes)
  :Signal Auction Service\nto extend by 2 minutes;
  :Broadcast extension notice\nto all subscribers;
endif

:Auction end time reached;
:Determine winner\n(highest valid bid);
:Broadcast auction-closed event;
:Notify Auction Service\nof final winner and amount;

|Buyer|
:Receive win / loss notification;
stop

@enduml
